<div class="media pixelfed">
  <div>
    <h2>pixelfed</h2>
    <a href="http://pixelfed.social/@amycatgirl">Follow</a>
  </div>
</div>
<p>
  I don't quite like the word "clone" to refer to a project but I'll try my best to describe this
  site.
</p>

<p>
  Pixelfed is a federated social media that's inspired by instagram. The site is media-first, which means that
  you can't post anything if it doesn't have at least one image or video attached to it, again, similar to
  Meta's Instagram.
</p>

<p>
  I post photos of my surroundings here. Cats, birds, the sky, the endless void that surrounds us, you name
  it. I also post my artwork and graphics design thingies from time to time to break the monotony of the
  account because I don't do <i>just</i> photography, do I?
</p>

<div class="media matrix">
  <div>
    <h2>matrix</h2>
    <a>@amycatgirl:catgirl.cloud</a>
  </div>
</div>

<p>
  Matrix (Not to be confused with the movie of the same name) is a federated chatting application that puts security first. Like Mastodon and Pixelfed, it can communicate to other servers that are also using matrix, but unlike those, Matrix uses it's own protocol, which means that you can't communicate with me from Mastodon or Misskey.
</p>

<p>
  I recently switched from revolt.chat due to issues with some of it's team members. I won't go too into it, but I would recomend to look it up on my Mastodon account.
</p>

